02:07.660 --> 02:16.060
that by clicking down here on the name and now call it relationships, like this and pressing enter

02:16.070 --> 02:17.510
of course in the end.

02:17.510 --> 02:24.940
Now if you press plus right here, you can add a second page and we will name that page measurers and

02:24.940 --> 02:26.180
press enter.

02:26.250 --> 02:27.480
Now that we got that,

02:27.490 --> 02:29.570
let's create a simple visualization,

02:29.620 --> 02:30.950
again our column chart.

02:31.090 --> 02:34.480
So I'm clicking right here and I'm positioning it right there,

02:34.480 --> 02:36.200
this is fine actually.

02:36.250 --> 02:41.820
Now if you go to the FACT-Population table in the fields column, you can find that total population measure

02:41.820 --> 02:45.350
right here with that calculator symbol in front of it.

02:45.490 --> 02:51.700
Now if you simply use it and drag it into the visualization for instance, then you can see it right here.

02:51.700 --> 02:54.030
Of course you don't have to drag it into a visualization,

02:54.040 --> 02:57.170
you can also put it right here into the value area,

02:57.370 --> 03:04.060
however this is not a really great visualization for the moment but it shows you that this measure works

03:04.120 --> 03:05.170
as soon as we use it

03:05.190 --> 03:06.880
in a visualization.

03:06.880 --> 03:08.510
Now let's go back to the data view,

03:08.590 --> 03:09.480
here we are

03:09.850 --> 03:14.500
and as a second measure, I would like to add the average population.

03:14.570 --> 03:17.650
Let's do that by clicking new measure again,

03:17.690 --> 03:24.980
now name it population average and you will see why I turn the name around this time and we will write that

03:24.980 --> 03:27.890
formula just as we did it with the sum formula.

03:28.040 --> 03:35.600
So we simply write average like this, press tab and now select again the FACT-Population table and the

03:35.600 --> 03:38.890
population column and press enter.

03:38.930 --> 03:42.090
Now we have the population average measure right here

03:42.350 --> 03:44.180
and I would like to rename that measure quickly,

03:44.180 --> 03:50.040
so I will simply select the total population measure, delete the total part right here and write

03:50.030 --> 03:53.270
population total and press enter.

03:53.270 --> 03:59.040
The reason why I'm doing this is that the names are sorted alphabetically right here and I want to keep

03:59.040 --> 04:02.510
the measures, so the population measures in that part.

04:02.540 --> 04:09.830
However if we now go back to our report view and create a new visualization by clicking here and writing

04:09.830 --> 04:10.740
it right there

04:11.280 --> 04:16.470
